WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.598
Open C-R-M, then Customers.

p02
00:00:02.910 --> 00:00:06.756
This is the member database, and it's where most support calls begin.

p03
00:00:07.013 --> 00:00:10.453
Every tool you need to find a customer sits on this one screen.

p04
00:00:10.919 --> 00:00:11.838
Start at the top.

p05
00:00:12.617 --> 00:00:14.455
Four numbers frame the whole base: total customers, active members, at risk, and prospects.

p06
00:00:14.812 --> 00:00:18.891
They cover every customer, not just the page in front of you.

p07
00:00:19.625 --> 00:00:23.947
Read them first.

p08
00:00:24.477 --> 00:00:25.543
Below the numbers, three cards.

p09
00:00:25.836 --> 00:00:26.685
One tracks member growth over the last year.

p10
00:00:27.211 --> 00:00:29.714
Another splits active members by plan.

p11
00:00:30.249 --> 00:00:32.678
The third grades customer health, low, medium, and high risk, at a glance.

p12
00:00:33.185 --> 00:00:41.278
You read these; you don't click into them.

p13
00:00:41.796 --> 00:00:43.159
Now the list card itself.

p14
00:00:43.766 --> 00:00:46.350
The eyebrow labels it the member database, and the title reads Customer List.

p15
00:00:46.742 --> 00:00:52.908
This card holds the searchable table of every customer you have.

p16
00:00:53.577 --> 00:00:55.596
Three buttons sit top-right of the card.

p17
00:00:56.295 --> 00:00:59.462
Retention Log opens a churn report we'll visit in a minute.

p18
00:01:00.431 --> 00:01:04.517
Delete and Add Customer both change data, so we leave them alone today.

p19
00:01:05.034 --> 00:01:06.960
Adding a customer gets its own lesson.

p20
00:01:07.527 --> 00:01:09.485
Just above the table, the search box.

p21
00:01:09.895 --> 00:01:10.998
Read the placeholder.

p22
00:01:11.447 --> 00:01:13.433
It names exactly what you can search by: a name, a plate, an email, a location, or a plan.

p23
00:01:13.757 --> 00:01:20.160
You never have to guess which field will match.

p24
00:01:20.744 --> 00:01:22.527
Next to it, the Filters control.

p25
00:01:23.059 --> 00:01:24.909
The badge counts active filters.

p26
00:01:25.314 --> 00:01:28.422
Right now it reads zero, so nothing is narrowing the list.

p27
00:01:29.003 --> 00:01:31.324
Open it for a panel that trims the base down;

p28
00:01:31.780 --> 00:01:35.660
any count above zero means the list is already filtered.

p29
00:01:35.660 --> 00:01:36.496
Now the columns.

p30
00:01:36.977 --> 00:01:37.542
Eight of them: customer, location, plan, member since, status,

p31
00:01:38.115 --> 00:01:38.655
then the member's numbers, visits, total spend, and last visit.

p32
00:01:38.937 --> 00:01:39.657
Every header sorts.

p33
00:01:39.985 --> 00:01:55.775
The checkbox column on the left selects rows, and on this tour those boxes stay empty.

p34
00:01:55.775 --> 00:01:57.168
Look at one row across.

p35
00:01:57.573 --> 00:02:00.918
The plan and the status each show as a coloured chip.

p36
00:02:01.537 --> 00:02:02.594
Active is green, inactive is grey, and the plan chip names the package.

p37
00:02:03.127 --> 00:02:11.396
The colour is how a row's state reads in a half-second.

p38
00:02:11.396 --> 00:02:12.201
Drop to the footer.

p39
00:02:12.737 --> 00:02:17.803
Twenty-five rows a page, and the last page button reads sixty-five thousand.

p40
00:02:18.498 --> 00:02:22.141
This table runs past a million and a half migrated records,

p41
00:02:22.468 --> 00:02:25.183
so you search for a customer, not page to them.

p42
00:02:26.065 --> 00:02:30.747
The strip up top counts a smaller headline figure that does not reconcile with the table,

p43
00:02:31.094 --> 00:02:35.115
a known demo quirk, which is why the two counts differ.

p44
00:02:35.115 --> 00:02:36.042
Click Retention Log.

p45
00:02:36.600 --> 00:02:40.098
This read-only page tracks members who left or nearly did.

p46
00:02:40.465 --> 00:02:42.218
Its own four numbers frame it: total events, saves this month, cancellations, and the churn rate.

p47
00:02:42.498 --> 00:02:46.806
No delete or add here.

p48
00:02:47.119 --> 00:02:52.016
It is a log you read, not a list you edit.

p49
00:02:52.016 --> 00:02:53.410
The table tells the story.

p50
00:02:53.888 --> 00:02:55.389
Each row is one event: date, customer, site, event type, and outcome.

p51
00:02:55.751 --> 00:02:59.425
A green Saved chip means you kept them, Cancelled means you lost them,

p52
00:02:59.732 --> 00:03:02.314
and Downgraded and At Risk fall in between.

p53
00:03:02.672 --> 00:03:11.634
When a churn question comes in, the answer lives here.

p54
00:03:11.634 --> 00:03:12.373
Head back to the list.

p55
00:03:13.078 --> 00:03:19.340
The breadcrumb or the sidebar both drop you on the Customer List again, right where you started.

p56
00:03:19.340 --> 00:03:20.044
Now use the search.

p57
00:03:20.520 --> 00:03:24.131
Type the first few letters of a name you can see, then hit Search.

p58
00:03:24.665 --> 00:03:26.860
The table collapses to just the matches.

p59
00:03:27.330 --> 00:03:32.480
On a list this size, that is how you land on the right customer in seconds.

p60
00:03:32.480 --> 00:03:33.307
Clear the box.

p61
00:03:33.699 --> 00:03:36.248
The full list snaps back, untouched.

p62
00:03:36.753 --> 00:03:38.270
That is the Customer List: numbers up top, health in the cards,

p63
00:03:38.647 --> 00:03:39.579
a search that names its own fields, sortable columns with colour-coded chips,

p64
00:03:39.887 --> 00:03:41.029
and a Retention Log one click away.

p65
00:03:41.479 --> 00:03:52.538
Learn this screen and C-R-M support gets faster.

